<?php

namespace Database\Seeders;

use App\Models\ContentBlock;
use Illuminate\Database\Seeder;

class ContentBlockSeeder extends Seeder
{
    /**
     * Seed the service pages' article content as editable blocks.
     *
     * Non-destructive: a page is only populated when it currently has NO
     * blocks. Pages the admin has already added to or edited are left
     * untouched, so running this seeder never wipes admin changes. This
     * makes it safe to run on every deploy to fill in any empty pages.
     *
     * To intentionally reset a page back to these defaults, delete its
     * blocks in the admin panel (or the DB) first, then re-run the seeder.
     */
    /**
     * The full default content for every page, keyed by page slug.
     * Exposed so the `content:reset` command can re-apply defaults.
     */
    public function data(): array
    {
        return [
            'heating' => $this->heating(),
            'cooling' => $this->cooling(),
            'plumbing' => $this->plumbing(),
            'electrical' => $this->electrical(),
            'indoor-air-quality' => $this->airQuality(),
            'drains' => $this->drains(),
            'commercial' => $this->commercial(),
        ];
    }

    public function run(): void
    {
        $pages = $this->data();

        foreach ($pages as $page => $blocks) {
            // Skip any page that already has content — preserves admin edits.
            if (ContentBlock::where('page', $page)->exists()) {
                continue;
            }

            foreach ($blocks as $i => $block) {
                ContentBlock::create(array_merge($block, ['page' => $page, 'position' => $i]));
            }
        }
    }

    private function heating(): array
    {
        return [
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Furnace Repair in NJ', 'body' => "<p>When your furnace quits on a freezing January night, you need furnace repair in NJ that shows up fast and gets it right the first time. Guardian Air is a licensed and insured heating company serving homeowners across <a href='/service-areas'>Monmouth, Middlesex, and Ocean counties</a> with same-day furnace repair, honest diagnostics, and upfront, flat-rate pricing — no overtime surprises and no pressure.</p><p>Our technicians repair every make and model of gas, electric, and oil furnace, and we also service <a href='/heating/boiler-repair'>boilers</a> and <a href='/heating/heat-pump'>heat pumps</a>. From a furnace that blows cold air to a unit that won't ignite at all, we pinpoint the real problem and fix it on the spot whenever possible, with common parts stocked on every truck.</p><p>Every furnace repair starts with a clear explanation of what's wrong and what it will cost. When a fix no longer makes sense, we'll walk you through <a href='/heating/furnace-replacement'>furnace replacement</a> — or you can <a href='/contact'>schedule service</a> online anytime.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Why Furnace Maintenance Matters', 'body' => "<p>Most no-heat emergencies are preventable. A short annual <a href='/heating/furnace-tune-up'>furnace tune-up</a> protects your comfort, your safety, and your wallet all winter long.</p><p><strong>Prevent Unexpected Breakdowns</strong> — Regular inspections catch worn parts early, before they turn into a no-heat <a href='/contact'>emergency</a> on the coldest night of the year.</p><p><strong>Improve Energy Efficiency</strong> — A clean, well-tuned furnace burns less fuel to heat your home; for year-round savings, ask about an efficient <a href='/heating/heat-pump'>heat pump</a>.</p><p><strong>Extend Equipment Lifespan</strong> — Consistent maintenance keeps your system running longer, delaying the cost of a full <a href='/heating/furnace-replacement'>furnace replacement</a> and protecting your warranty.</p><p><strong>Protect Your Family's Safety</strong> — A maintenance visit includes a carbon monoxide and heat-exchanger check. <a href='/contact'>Schedule your tune-up</a> in early fall, before the first cold snap.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'image', 'heading' => 'Guardian Air technician performing furnace repair in a New Jersey home', 'image_path' => '/img/heating-hero.webp'],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'When to Replace Your Furnace', 'body' => "<p>Deciding whether to repair or replace your furnace can be tough. These signs usually mean <a href='/heating/furnace-replacement'>furnace replacement</a> is the smarter long-term investment.</p><p><strong>Age</strong> — If your furnace is more than 15 years old, it's far less efficient than modern units. Newer <a href='/heating/furnace-replacement'>high-efficiency systems</a> can noticeably cut your heating bills.</p><p><strong>Frequent Repairs</strong> — If you're calling for repairs every season, a new system often costs less over time, and regular <a href='/heating/furnace-tune-up'>maintenance</a> helps prevent breakdowns.</p><p><strong>Uneven or Weak Heat</strong> — Cold spots and rooms that never warm up are a sign your furnace can't keep up. A <a href='/heating/heat-pump'>heat pump</a> is one efficient alternative we install.</p><p><strong>Rising Energy Bills</strong> — An unexplained jump in heating costs usually means lost efficiency. We serve homeowners across <a href='/service-areas'>central New Jersey</a> with honest assessments.</p><p>Not sure which way to go? <a href='/contact'>Contact us</a> for a free replacement estimate — never a hard sell.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Heating Systems We Service', 'body' => "<p>Our licensed technicians install, repair, and maintain every major type of home heating system across <a href='/service-areas'>New Jersey</a>.</p><p><strong>Gas Furnaces</strong> — The most common and cost-effective option, burning natural gas for fast, powerful, whole-home heat.</p><p><strong>Oil Furnaces</strong> — Common in older New Jersey homes, delivering strong, reliable heat output; we service and tune oil systems of every age.</p><p><strong>Electric Furnaces</strong> — A great fit for homes without a gas line, using electric heating elements for clean, simple heat.</p><p><strong><a href='/heating/heat-pump'>Heat Pumps</a></strong> — Energy-efficient electric systems that both heat and cool, ideal for year-round comfort and lower operating costs.</p><p><strong><a href='/heating/boiler-repair'>Boilers</a></strong> — Steady radiant warmth through hot water; we repair leaks, pressure problems, and no-heat issues. Considering an upgrade? Explore our <a href='/heating/furnace-replacement'>furnace replacement</a> options or book a <a href='/heating/furnace-tune-up'>furnace tune-up</a>.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'No-Heat Emergency Service 24/7', 'body' => "<p>A heating failure in the middle of a New Jersey winter can't wait until morning. That's why Guardian Air offers 24/7 no-heat emergency furnace repair across <a href='/service-areas'>Monmouth, Middlesex, and Ocean counties</a>.</p><p>When you call, you reach a real person who dispatches a licensed technician fast — stocked to handle most repairs on the first visit, whether it's your furnace, a <a href='/heating/boiler-repair'>boiler</a>, or a failed safety switch.</p><p>And because our pricing is flat-rate, you'll never pay extra for nights, weekends, or holidays. <a href='/contact'>Schedule emergency service</a> when you need it most.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Serving Monmouth, Middlesex & Ocean County', 'body' => "<p>Guardian Air provides trusted furnace repair and heating service to homeowners throughout <a href='/service-areas'>central New Jersey</a>. Our technicians are local, which means faster response times and a team that knows the older oil systems and newer high-efficiency furnaces common to the area.</p><p>We proudly serve <a href='/heating/toms-river'>Toms River</a>, <a href='/heating/freehold'>Freehold</a>, <a href='/heating/brick'>Brick</a>, <a href='/heating/old-bridge'>Old Bridge</a>, <a href='/heating/red-bank'>Red Bank</a>, and <a href='/heating/lakewood'>Lakewood</a>, along with surrounding communities across all three counties.</p><p>Don't see your town listed? We almost certainly still serve it — <a href='/contact'>give us a call</a> to confirm and schedule your furnace repair or tune-up today.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'How much does furnace repair cost in NJ?', 'body' => 'Most furnace repairs in New Jersey fall between $150 and $750 depending on the failed part — an igniter or flame sensor is on the lower end, while a blower motor or control board is higher. We always provide a flat-rate quote before any work begins, so you know the full cost upfront with no surprises.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'When should I replace my furnace instead of repairing it?', 'body' => 'Replacement usually makes sense when your furnace is over 15 years old, needs frequent or expensive repairs, heats unevenly, or is driving up your energy bills. If a single repair is minor and the system is otherwise healthy, fixing it is the better value. We give you an honest recommendation either way.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Why does my furnace keep shutting off?', 'body' => 'Short-cycling is most often caused by a dirty air filter restricting airflow, a malfunctioning thermostat, a clogged flue, or an overheating safety switch doing its job. A quick diagnostic visit pinpoints the exact cause and prevents further wear on the system.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Should I choose an oil or gas furnace?', 'body' => 'Gas furnaces are typically cheaper to run and lower-maintenance where a natural gas line is available, which is why most New Jersey homeowners choose them. Oil furnaces remain a strong option for homes without gas service and can deliver very high heat output. We help you compare based on your home and local fuel costs.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'How long does a furnace installation take?', 'body' => 'A standard furnace replacement is usually completed in a single day — typically four to eight hours. More involved jobs, such as switching fuel types or modifying ductwork, may take longer. We give you a clear timeline with your free estimate.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'What areas do you serve for furnace repair?', 'body' => 'We provide furnace repair and heating service across Monmouth, Middlesex, and Ocean counties, including Toms River, Freehold, Brick, Old Bridge, Red Bank, Lakewood, and the surrounding towns. Call us to confirm service to your specific address.'],
        ];
    }

    private function cooling(): array
    {
        return [
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'AC Repair in NJ', 'body' => "<p>When your air conditioner blows warm air in the middle of a July heatwave, you need AC repair in NJ that responds fast and fixes it right. Guardian Air is a licensed and insured cooling company serving homeowners across <a href='/service-areas'>Monmouth, Middlesex, and Ocean counties</a> with same-day repair, honest diagnostics, and upfront, flat-rate pricing.</p><p>We repair every major brand of central air, <a href='/heating/heat-pump'>heat pump</a>, and <a href='/cooling/ductless-mini-split'>ductless system</a>. Whether your AC won't turn on, short-cycles, or can't keep up, we pinpoint the real cause and fix it on the spot whenever possible, with common parts stocked on every truck.</p><p>Every repair begins with a clear explanation and a flat-rate quote — see typical pricing in our <a href='/cost-guides/ac-repair-cost'>AC repair cost guide</a>. It's cooling service the way it should be: fast, fair, and backed by a local team your neighbors trust.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Why AC Maintenance Matters', 'body' => "<p>Most summer breakdowns are preventable. A short annual <a href='/cooling/ac-tune-up'>AC tune-up</a> keeps your air conditioner cooling efficiently when you need it most.</p><p><strong>Prevent Unexpected Breakdowns</strong> — Regular tune-ups catch worn parts early, before they leave you needing <a href='/contact'>emergency service</a> on the hottest day of the summer.</p><p><strong>Improve Energy Efficiency</strong> — A clean, well-charged system cools using far less electricity; for year-round savings, consider an efficient <a href='/heating/heat-pump'>heat pump</a>.</p><p><strong>Extend Equipment Lifespan</strong> — Consistent maintenance delays the cost of a full <a href='/cooling/ac-installation'>AC replacement</a> and protects your warranty.</p><p><strong>Better Air Quality</strong> — Cleaning coils and replacing filters means cleaner air; pair it with <a href='/indoor-air-quality'>indoor air quality</a> solutions for the whole home.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'image', 'heading' => 'Guardian Air technician performing AC repair on an outdoor unit in New Jersey', 'image_path' => '/img/cooling-hero.webp'],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'When to Replace Your AC', 'body' => "<p>Deciding whether to repair or replace your air conditioner can be tough. These signs usually point to <a href='/cooling/ac-installation'>replacement</a> as the smarter long-term investment.</p><p><strong>Age</strong> — If your AC is more than 12 to 15 years old, a new <a href='/cooling/ac-installation'>high-efficiency system</a> can noticeably lower your cooling bills.</p><p><strong>Frequent Repairs</strong> — If you're calling every summer, the repair costs (see our <a href='/cost-guides/ac-repair-cost'>cost guide</a>) often add up to more than a reliable new system.</p><p><strong>Uneven Cooling</strong> — Hot spots and rooms that never cool down may call for zoned comfort like a <a href='/cooling/ductless-mini-split'>ductless mini-split</a>.</p><p><strong>Rising Energy Bills</strong> — A jump in cooling costs usually means lost efficiency; our local techs across <a href='/service-areas'>central NJ</a> give honest assessments.</p><p>Not sure which way to go? <a href='/contact'>Contact us</a> for a free replacement estimate — never a hard sell.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Cooling Systems We Service', 'body' => "<p>Our licensed technicians install, repair, and maintain every major type of home cooling system across <a href='/service-areas'>New Jersey</a>.</p><p><strong>Central Air Conditioning</strong> — The most popular whole-home option; we handle repair and <a href='/cooling/ac-installation'>installation</a> through your existing ductwork.</p><p><strong>Heat Pumps</strong> — Energy-efficient systems that both cool and heat; learn more on our <a href='/heating/heat-pump'>heat pump</a> page.</p><p><strong>Ductless Mini-Splits</strong> — A flexible choice for homes without ductwork or for specific rooms — see <a href='/cooling/ductless-mini-split'>ductless mini-splits</a>.</p><p><strong>Window & Wall Units</strong> — A lower-cost option for individual rooms, perfect for supplementing your <a href='/cooling/ac-installation'>main system</a>.</p><p><strong>Dual-Zone Systems</strong> — Independently control different areas of your home; keep them efficient with a yearly <a href='/cooling/ac-tune-up'>tune-up</a>.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Common AC Problems We Fix', 'body' => "<p>Air conditioners fail in predictable ways, and our technicians diagnose and repair them every day across <a href='/service-areas'>New Jersey</a>.</p><p><strong>AC Blowing Warm Air</strong> — Usually a thermostat setting, low refrigerant, or a dirty coil; see costs in our <a href='/cost-guides/ac-repair-cost'>AC repair cost guide</a>.</p><p><strong>AC Won't Turn On</strong> — Often a tripped breaker, a failed capacitor or contactor, or a control board — <a href='/contact'>schedule a diagnostic</a>.</p><p><strong>Water Leaks</strong> — Typically a clogged condensate line or full drain pan; regular <a href='/cooling/ac-tune-up'>maintenance</a> prevents it.</p><p><strong>Frozen Coils</strong> — Caused by restricted airflow or low refrigerant; a <a href='/cooling/ac-tune-up'>tune-up</a> finds the root cause.</p><p><strong>Strange Noises or Odors</strong> — Musty smells can signal mold — pair repair with <a href='/indoor-air-quality'>indoor air quality</a> service.</p>"],
