            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'How much does AC repair cost in NJ?', 'body' => 'Most AC repairs in New Jersey range from $150 to $600 depending on the part — a capacitor or contactor is on the lower end, while a refrigerant recharge or compressor work is higher. We always provide a flat-rate quote before any work begins, so you know the full cost upfront with no surprises.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Why is my AC blowing warm air?', 'body' => 'The most common causes are a thermostat set incorrectly, a clogged air filter, low refrigerant from a leak, a dirty condenser coil, or a frozen evaporator coil. A quick diagnostic pinpoints the exact issue so we can fix it fast.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Should I repair or replace my air conditioner?', 'body' => 'If your unit is under 10 years old and the repair is minor, fixing it usually makes sense. For older systems with frequent breakdowns or an expensive repair like a compressor, replacement is often the smarter long-term investment. We give you an honest recommendation either way.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'What size air conditioner does my home need?', 'body' => 'Proper AC sizing depends on your home\'s square footage, insulation, windows, and layout — not just a rule of thumb. An undersized unit struggles in heat, while an oversized one short-cycles and wastes energy. We perform a load calculation to recommend the right size for your home.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Do you offer emergency AC repair in Monmouth County?', 'body' => 'Yes. We provide fast emergency AC repair across Monmouth County and the surrounding areas, including Freehold, Red Bank, Middletown, and Howell. Call us and we\'ll dispatch a licensed technician as quickly as possible — at the same flat rate, day or night.'],
        ];
    }

