            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Plumber in Freehold & Monmouth County', 'body' => "<p>Across Monmouth County, homeowners in <a href='/plumbing/freehold'>Freehold</a>, <a href='/plumbing/red-bank'>Red Bank</a>, and the surrounding area rely on Guardian Air for dependable plumbing service. We also serve <a href='/plumbing/old-bridge'>Old Bridge</a> and the rest of <a href='/plumbing/middlesex-county'>Middlesex County</a>.</p><p>From routine repairs to <a href='/plumbing/emergency-plumber'>24/7 emergencies</a>, our licensed plumbers deliver the same upfront pricing on every job. Browse all our <a href='/service-areas'>service areas</a> — don't see your town? We almost certainly still serve it, so give us a call today.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'How much does an emergency plumber cost in NJ?', 'body' => 'Emergency plumbing in New Jersey typically ranges from about $150 to $500+ depending on the problem and the parts needed. Guardian Air charges flat-rate pricing with no extra fees for nights, weekends, or holidays, and we give you the full quote before any work begins.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Do you offer 24-hour plumbing service in Monmouth County?', 'body' => 'Yes. We provide 24-hour emergency plumbing across Monmouth County, including Freehold, Red Bank, Middletown, and Howell. Call any time and we\'ll dispatch a licensed plumber as quickly as possible to stop the damage and fix the problem.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'What are the signs of a slab leak?', 'body' => 'Common signs of a slab leak include warm spots on the floor, the sound of running water when nothing is on, an unexplained spike in your water bill, cracks in flooring or walls, and damp or warped areas. We use non-invasive leak detection to confirm and locate it before repairing.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Can you repair a tankless water heater?', 'body' => 'Yes. We repair and maintain tankless water heaters from all major brands — addressing error codes, scale buildup, ignition issues, and flow problems. If a unit is beyond economical repair, we\'ll recommend and install a reliable replacement.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'What plumbing services do you offer in Toms River?', 'body' => 'In Toms River and the surrounding Ocean County area we offer the full range of residential plumbing: emergency repairs, water heater repair and replacement, leak detection, pipe repair and repiping, drain cleaning, and fixture installation — all with flat-rate pricing.'],
        ];
    }

    private function electrical(): array
    {
        return [
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Electrical Service Overview', 'body' => "Electrical work is not a DIY project. Whether you need a panel upgrade to handle modern appliances, new outlets for a home office, or emergency repairs for a tripped breaker, our licensed electricians deliver safe, code-compliant work every time.\n\nWe handle residential and light commercial electrical projects of all sizes. Every job starts with a thorough inspection and a flat-rate quote. We explain what needs to be done, why it matters for your safety, and what it will cost — before we touch a single wire."],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Why Electrical Safety Matters', 'body' => "Your home's electrical system powers everything you rely on, and when it's neglected, the risks add up fast. Staying on top of it protects your home and your family.\n\nPrevent Electrical Fires — Faulty wiring and overloaded circuits are a leading cause of home fires. Regular inspections catch hidden hazards before they become dangerous.\n\nProtect Your Appliances — Proper wiring and surge protection shield your electronics and appliances from damaging power spikes, extending their lifespan.\n\nStay Code-Compliant — Outdated or DIY wiring can fail inspection and void insurance. Licensed work keeps your home up to current electrical code and safe for your family."],
            ['type' => 'image', 'heading' => 'Guardian Air electrician working on a residential electrical panel in New Jersey', 'image_path' => '/img/electrical.webp'],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Signs You Need An Electrician', 'body' => "Electrical problems rarely fix themselves. Watch for these warning signs that it's time to call a licensed pro.\n\nFrequent Tripping — Breakers that trip repeatedly or fuses that blow often signal an overloaded circuit or a wiring fault that needs professional attention.\n\nFlickering or Dimming Lights — Lights that flicker or dim when appliances turn on point to loose connections, an overloaded panel, or aging wiring.\n\nWarm Outlets or Burning Smell — Outlets or switches that feel warm, spark, or give off a burning odor are serious fire hazards. Shut off the circuit and call us right away.\n\nOutdated Panel or Wiring — Homes with a fuse box, aluminum wiring, or a panel under 100 amps often can't safely handle modern electrical demands.\n\nNoticing any of these in your home? Schedule an electrical inspection and we'll get to the root of it."],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Electrical Services We Offer', 'body' => "Here's a quick guide to the electrical work we install, repair, and maintain.\n\nPanel Upgrades — Modernize your electrical panel to safely handle today's appliances, EV chargers, and high-demand circuits with confidence.\n\nWiring & Rewiring — New circuits, full-home rewires, and repairs to damaged or outdated wiring, all done to current code for lasting safety.\n\nLighting & Fixtures — Recessed lighting, ceiling fans, outdoor and accent fixtures installed cleanly to brighten and elevate every room.\n\nOutlets & Switches — New outlets, GFCI installations, dimmers, and smart switches added wherever you need safe, convenient power.\n\nGenerators & EV Chargers — Standby generator hookups and Level 2 EV charger installs that keep you powered and ready for the future."],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'How do I know if my electrical panel needs an upgrade?', 'body' => 'If you have a fuse box, a panel rated under 100 amps, frequently tripping breakers, or you\'re adding major appliances or an EV charger, it\'s likely time for an upgrade. We can assess your panel and recommend the right capacity for your home.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Why do my circuit breakers keep tripping?', 'body' => 'Repeated tripping usually means a circuit is overloaded, or there\'s a short circuit or ground fault. It\'s the breaker doing its job, but persistent tripping points to an underlying issue a licensed electrician should diagnose.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Is it safe to do my own electrical work?', 'body' => 'Swapping a light bulb or resetting a tripped breaker is fine. Anything involving wiring, outlets, panels, or new circuits should be left to a licensed electrician — DIY electrical mistakes can cause fires, shocks, and failed inspections.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'What causes flickering or dimming lights?', 'body' => 'Flickering often comes from loose wiring, an overloaded circuit, a failing fixture, or a panel that can\'t keep up with demand. If it happens throughout the house, it\'s worth having the system inspected.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Why do my outlets feel warm or spark?', 'body' => 'A warm outlet, sparking, or a burning smell signals loose connections, overloading, or damaged wiring, all serious fire risks. Stop using the outlet, turn off the circuit, and call us for same-day service.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'What is a GFCI outlet and where do I need them?', 'body' => 'A GFCI (Ground Fault Circuit Interrupter) outlet shuts off power instantly if it detects a fault, preventing shocks. Code requires them in kitchens, bathrooms, garages, basements, and outdoor areas.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Can you install an EV charger at my home?', 'body' => 'Yes. We install Level 2 EV chargers, including any panel upgrades or dedicated circuits needed to support them safely. We\'ll evaluate your panel capacity and recommend the best setup for your vehicle.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Do I need a permit for electrical work?', 'body' => 'Most electrical work — panel upgrades, new circuits, and rewiring — requires a permit and inspection. As licensed electricians, we handle the permitting process and ensure every job passes inspection.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => "How often should I have my home's wiring inspected?", 'body' => "We recommend an inspection every few years for newer homes, and sooner for homes over 25 years old or any home you've just purchased. Aluminum wiring and older panels should be checked promptly."],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'What should I do during an electrical emergency?', 'body' => 'If you smell burning, see sparks, or have exposed wiring, shut off power at the breaker if it\'s safe to do so and keep away from the area. Then call us — we offer same-day emergency electrical service.'],
        ];
    }

    private function airQuality(): array
    {
        return [
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Air Quality Testing NJ', 'body' => "<p>If your family is dealing with constant dust, allergies, or musty odors, professional air quality testing in NJ is the first step to a healthier home. Guardian Air serves homeowners across <a href='/service-areas'>Monmouth, Middlesex, and Ocean counties</a> — we test, diagnose, and fix the air you breathe.</p><p>The air inside your home can be up to five times more polluted than outside. Dust, pollen, dander, mold spores, and VOCs all circulate through your HVAC system. We assess your home and recommend the right mix of filtration, humidity control, and purification — and may suggest <a href='/indoor-air-quality/mold-testing'>mold testing</a> when moisture is involved.</p><p>From whole-home <a href='/indoor-air-quality/air-purifier'>air purifiers</a> and UV lights to <a href='/indoor-air-quality/duct-cleaning'>air duct cleaning</a>, we have a solution for every concern and budget.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Signs of Poor Air Quality', 'body' => "<p>Poor indoor air quality isn't always obvious. Watch for these warning signs — and <a href='/contact'>schedule an assessment</a> if you notice them.</p><p><strong>Persistent Dust</strong> — If dust resettles right after cleaning, your air is full of fine particles that <a href='/indoor-air-quality/duct-cleaning'>duct cleaning</a> and better filtration help remove.</p><p><strong>Allergy & Respiratory Symptoms</strong> — Sneezing, congestion, or irritated eyes indoors point to pollen and dander an <a href='/indoor-air-quality/air-purifier'>air purifier</a> can capture.</p><p><strong>Musty or Stale Odors</strong> — Lingering smells can signal mold or moisture that calls for <a href='/indoor-air-quality/mold-testing'>mold testing</a>.</p><p><strong>Humidity Problems</strong> — Condensation, clammy air, or overly dry air mean your home needs <a href='/indoor-air-quality/humidifier-dehumidifier'>humidity control</a>.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'image', 'heading' => 'Guardian Air technician performing indoor air quality testing in a New Jersey home', 'image_path' => '/img/air-quality-hero.webp'],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Air Quality Solutions for NJ Homes', 'body' => "<p>Based on your testing results, we install and service the full range of indoor air quality solutions across <a href='/service-areas'>New Jersey</a>.</p><p><strong>Air Purifiers</strong> — Whole-home <a href='/indoor-air-quality/air-purifier'>air purifier</a> systems that capture allergens, dust, smoke, and microscopic particles.</p><p><strong>Mold Testing & Guidance</strong> — We identify hidden moisture and mold with <a href='/indoor-air-quality/mold-testing'>mold testing</a> and lay out a clear plan to resolve it.</p><p><strong>Duct Cleaning</strong> — <a href='/indoor-air-quality/duct-cleaning'>Air duct cleaning</a> clears built-up dust and allergens so every room breathes cleaner.</p><p><strong>Humidifiers & Dehumidifiers</strong> — <a href='/indoor-air-quality/humidifier-dehumidifier'>Whole-home humidity control</a> keeps your home at a healthy, comfortable balance year-round.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Why NJ Homes Need IAQ', 'body' => "<p>New Jersey's humid summers and tightly sealed winters create the perfect conditions for poor indoor air quality — which is why <a href='/indoor-air-quality/duct-cleaning'>duct cleaning</a> and filtration pay off every day.</p><p><strong>Protect Your Health</strong> — Cleaner air reduces the allergens and irritants that aggravate asthma and allergies; an <a href='/indoor-air-quality/air-purifier'>air purifier</a> helps most.</p><p><strong>Breathe Easier Every Day</strong> — Balanced <a href='/indoor-air-quality/humidifier-dehumidifier'>humidity</a> and proper filtration help your family sleep better and feel more comfortable.</p><p><strong>Protect Your Home & HVAC</strong> — Controlling dust and moisture keeps your <a href='/heating'>HVAC system</a> efficient and helps prevent mold damage.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Serving Monmouth, Middlesex & Ocean County', 'body' => "<p>Guardian Air provides indoor air quality testing and solutions to homeowners throughout central New Jersey. Because our technicians are local, we understand the seasonal humidity, pollen, and older-home conditions that affect air quality across the region.</p><p>We proudly serve <a href='/indoor-air-quality/toms-river'>Toms River</a>, <a href='/indoor-air-quality/freehold'>Freehold</a>, <a href='/indoor-air-quality/brick'>Brick</a>, <a href='/indoor-air-quality/old-bridge'>Old Bridge</a>, <a href='/indoor-air-quality/red-bank'>Red Bank</a>, and <a href='/indoor-air-quality/lakewood'>Lakewood</a>, across all three counties. Browse all our <a href='/service-areas'>service areas</a> to find your town.</p><p>Explore our specific solutions — <a href='/indoor-air-quality/duct-cleaning'>air duct cleaning</a>, <a href='/indoor-air-quality/mold-testing'>mold testing</a>, and <a href='/indoor-air-quality/air-purifier'>air purifiers</a>. Don't see your town listed? We almost certainly still serve it — call to schedule your air quality assessment today.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'How much does air quality testing cost in NJ?', 'body' => 'Indoor air quality assessments in New Jersey typically range from a complimentary visual evaluation to a few hundred dollars for detailed testing of particulates, humidity, and contaminants. We explain your options upfront and recommend only what your home actually needs.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'What are the most common indoor air pollutants in NJ homes?', 'body' => 'The most common culprits are dust, pollen, pet dander, mold spores, and volatile organic compounds (VOCs) from cleaning products and building materials. New Jersey\'s humid summers also encourage mold and dust mites, while tightly sealed winters trap pollutants indoors.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Does my HVAC filter really affect air quality?', 'body' => 'Yes — significantly. A clogged or low-grade filter lets fine particles recirculate through your home. Most filters should be changed every one to three months, and upgrading to a higher-efficiency (higher-MERV) filter can noticeably improve the air, as long as your system is rated for it.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'What is the best air purifier for a whole house?', 'body' => 'For whole-home coverage, a media air purifier or UV-equipped system installed directly into your HVAC ductwork outperforms portable units because it treats all the air your system moves. We size the right solution based on your home and specific air quality concerns.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'What is the ideal indoor humidity level?', 'body' => 'Most homes are most comfortable between 30% and 50% relative humidity. Too low causes dry skin and static; too high encourages mold and dust mites. Whole-home humidifiers and dehumidifiers help you maintain the right balance year-round.'],
        ];
    }

    private function drains(): array
    {
        return [
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Drain Cleaning Services in NJ', 'body' => "<p>Need fast, reliable drain cleaning in NJ? Guardian Air is a licensed and insured drain and sewer company serving homeowners across <a href='/service-areas'>Monmouth, Middlesex, and Ocean counties</a>. A backed-up line can damage your home, so we clear it completely instead of punching a temporary hole through the clog.</p><p>When needed, we start with a <a href='/drains/camera-inspection'>camera inspection</a> to see the real cause, then use the right tool — from motorized snaking to <a href='/drains/hydro-jetting'>hydro jetting</a>. Every job comes with upfront, flat-rate pricing — see our <a href='/cost-guides/drain-cleaning-cost'>drain cleaning cost guide</a>.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Signs of a Drain Problem', 'body' => "<p>Catching a drain issue early saves you from a messy, expensive backup — <a href='/contact'>schedule service</a> at the first warning sign.</p><p><strong>Slow Drainage</strong> — Water that pools and drains slowly is the earliest sign of a developing clog we can clear with <a href='/drains'>drain cleaning</a>.</p><p><strong>Gurgling Sounds</strong> — Bubbling noises mean air is trapped behind a blockage; a <a href='/drains/camera-inspection'>camera inspection</a> locates it.</p><p><strong>Foul Odors</strong> — Persistent sewage smells usually point to trapped debris or a partial blockage that may need <a href='/drains/hydro-jetting'>hydro jetting</a>.</p><p><strong>Frequent Clogs</strong> — If you're plunging the same drain repeatedly, the real problem is deeper in the line and may call for <a href='/drains/sewer-repair'>sewer repair</a>.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'image', 'heading' => 'Guardian Air technician performing drain cleaning in a New Jersey home', 'image_path' => '/img/drains-hero.webp'],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Drain Cleaning in Monmouth & Middlesex County', 'body' => "<p>Guardian Air provides trusted drain cleaning throughout Monmouth and Middlesex counties. Homeowners in <a href='/drains/freehold'>Freehold</a>, <a href='/drains/red-bank'>Red Bank</a>, and <a href='/drains/old-bridge'>Old Bridge</a> rely on us for fast, clean drain and sewer service — as do families across <a href='/drains/toms-river'>Toms River</a>, <a href='/drains/brick'>Brick</a>, and <a href='/drains/lakewood'>Lakewood</a>.</p><p>From a clogged kitchen sink to a backed-up main line needing <a href='/drains/hydro-jetting'>hydro jetting</a> or <a href='/drains/sewer-repair'>sewer repair</a>, our local technicians clear it the first time. Browse all our <a href='/service-areas'>service areas</a> — help is never far away when a drain emergency strikes.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Sewer Repair & Line Replacement', 'body' => "<p>A failing sewer line causes repeat backups, foul odors, and serious health hazards. From spot repairs to full line replacement, our <a href='/drains/sewer-repair'>sewer repair</a> service fixes cracked, collapsed, and root-invaded lines and restores reliable flow.</p><p>Tree roots are a common culprit in older neighborhoods across <a href='/service-areas'>New Jersey</a>. A <a href='/drains/camera-inspection'>camera inspection</a> confirms the issue so we recommend the right repair, not a guess.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Hydro Jetting', 'body' => "<p>Our <a href='/drains/hydro-jetting'>hydro jetting</a> service uses high-pressure water to scour the inside of your pipes clean — blasting away grease, scale, and roots that snaking leaves behind. It's the most thorough fix for stubborn and recurring clogs.</p><p>If you find yourself clearing the same drain again and again, hydro jetting restores the line to like-new flow — and our <a href='/cost-guides/drain-cleaning-cost'>cost guide</a> shows what to expect.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Camera Inspection', 'body' => "<p>A waterproof <a href='/drains/camera-inspection'>camera inspection</a> travels through your line so you can see the exact cause and location of a problem — no demolition guesswork.</p><p>We use it to diagnose chronic clogs, locate breaks and root intrusion, and verify the line is clear after <a href='/drains/sewer-repair'>sewer repair</a> — the smartest way to confirm what's happening before spending money.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Emergency Drain Service', 'body' => "<p>When a main line backs up or a drain floods, it can't wait. Guardian Air offers same-day and 24/7 emergency drain service across <a href='/service-areas'>Monmouth, Middlesex, and Ocean counties</a>.</p><p>Call and you'll reach a real person who dispatches a technician fast to clear the blockage and protect your home — at the same flat rate, day or night. <a href='/contact'>Schedule service</a> now.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'How much does drain cleaning cost in NJ?', 'body' => 'Most drain cleaning in New Jersey ranges from about $150 to $500 depending on the location and severity of the clog, with hydro jetting on the higher end. We provide a flat-rate quote upfront with no hidden fees, so you know the cost before we start.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'What are the signs I need a sewer line replacement?', 'body' => 'Frequent main-line backups, multiple drains clogging at once, sewage odors, soggy patches in the yard, and recurring root intrusion all point to a failing sewer line. A camera inspection confirms whether a spot repair will do or full replacement is needed.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Why do my drains keep clogging?', 'body' => 'Chronic clogs are usually caused by grease buildup, hair, soap scum, mineral scale, or tree roots in the main line. A one-time clearing may not solve a deeper issue, so we inspect the line to find and fix the real cause — often with hydro jetting.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Do you offer emergency drain service in Monmouth County?', 'body' => 'Yes. We provide same-day and 24/7 emergency drain and sewer service across Monmouth County, including Freehold, Red Bank, Middletown, and Howell. Call any time and we\'ll dispatch a technician quickly at our standard flat rate.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Is hydro jetting better than snaking?', 'body' => 'Snaking is great for breaking through a single clog quickly, while hydro jetting cleans the entire interior of the pipe, removing grease, scale, and roots. For recurring or severe clogs, hydro jetting delivers a more thorough, longer-lasting result.'],
        ];
    }

    private function commercial(): array
    {
        return [
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Commercial HVAC Repair & Emergency', 'body' => "<p>When your commercial HVAC system fails on a 95-degree day, every minute of downtime costs money. Guardian Air provides fast <a href='/commercial-hvac/repair'>commercial HVAC repair</a> for businesses across <a href='/service-areas'>Monmouth, Middlesex, and Ocean counties</a>.</p><p>Our technicians repair rooftop units (RTUs), boilers, chillers, and split systems of every size. We're available 24/7, and <a href='/commercial-hvac/maintenance-contracts'>maintenance-plan clients</a> receive priority dispatch — in most cases a technician on-site the same day.</p><p>Every call starts with a clear diagnosis and a written quote, so there are no surprises — just honest commercial service. <a href='/contact'>Request service</a> any time.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Commercial HVAC Installation', 'body' => "<p>Whether you're outfitting a new build, replacing an aging rooftop unit, or upgrading to high-efficiency, our team handles commercial HVAC installation from load calculation to startup across <a href='/service-areas'>New Jersey</a>.</p><p>We properly size every system to your facility's square footage and usage — an undersized unit struggles and an oversized one wastes energy. Protect that investment with a <a href='/commercial-hvac/maintenance-contracts'>maintenance contract</a> after install.</p><p>We coordinate around your business hours and handle permitting and code compliance. <a href='/contact'>Get a free assessment</a> for your facility.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'image', 'heading' => 'Guardian Air commercial technician servicing a rooftop HVAC unit in New Jersey', 'image_path' => '/img/commercial-hero.webp'],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Preventive Maintenance Contracts', 'body' => "<p>For a business, unexpected equipment failure means lost revenue. A scheduled <a href='/commercial-hvac/maintenance-contracts'>preventive maintenance contract</a> protects your operation and your bottom line.</p><p><strong>Reduce Costly Downtime</strong> — Scheduled inspections catch small failures early, before they shut you down during peak hours and force an <a href='/commercial-hvac/repair'>emergency repair</a>.</p><p><strong>Lower Operating Costs</strong> — Well-maintained systems run more efficiently, cutting energy bills across your <a href='/service-areas'>NJ</a> locations.</p><p><strong>Protect Your Investment</strong> — Routine service extends the life of rooftop units, boilers, and chillers, and keeps warranties valid. <a href='/contact'>Ask about a plan</a> for your equipment.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Industries We Serve', 'body' => "<p>We tailor our <a href='/commercial-hvac'>commercial HVAC</a> and <a href='/commercial-plumbing'>plumbing</a> service to the unique demands of each type of facility.</p><p><strong>Offices & Professional Buildings</strong> — Consistent comfort for tenants and staff, with discreet scheduling backed by a <a href='/commercial-hvac/maintenance-contracts'>maintenance plan</a>.</p><p><strong>Restaurants & Food Service</strong> — Make-up air, refrigeration, and rooftop service that meets health-code standards — plus fast <a href='/commercial-hvac/repair'>repair</a> when the kitchen can't stop.</p><p><strong>Retail & Shopping Centers</strong> — Reliable heating and cooling across <a href='/service-areas'>central NJ</a> that keeps customers comfortable.</p><p><strong>Multi-Family & Property Management</strong> — Building-wide HVAC maintenance with fast response — <a href='/contact'>tell us about your property</a>.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Commercial Boiler & Heating', 'body' => "<p>Larger facilities depend on commercial boilers that can't fail in a New Jersey winter. We service, repair, and replace hydronic and steam boilers, rooftop heating units, and make-up air systems — book it through <a href='/commercial-hvac/repair'>commercial HVAC repair</a>.</p><p>From pressure and leak diagnostics to full boiler replacement, our technicians keep your building warm and efficient. We also handle <a href='/commercial-plumbing'>commercial plumbing</a> sized for a busy property.</p><p>Regular maintenance keeps your heat reliable and costs down — see our <a href='/commercial-hvac/maintenance-contracts'>maintenance contracts</a>.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Serving Businesses in Monmouth, Middlesex & Ocean County', 'body' => "<p>Guardian Air serves commercial clients throughout central New Jersey, including <a href='/commercial-hvac/toms-river'>Toms River</a>, <a href='/commercial-hvac/freehold'>Freehold</a>, and <a href='/commercial-hvac/brick'>Brick</a>, plus all of <a href='/commercial-hvac/monmouth-county'>Monmouth</a>, <a href='/commercial-hvac/middlesex-county'>Middlesex</a>, and <a href='/commercial-hvac/ocean-county'>Ocean</a> counties. Because our technicians are local, we respond fast when your business needs us.</p><p>Our team is licensed and insured for commercial work, NATE-certified, and EPA 608 certified for refrigerant handling — the B2B credentials property managers expect. Explore our <a href='/commercial-hvac/maintenance-contracts'>maintenance contracts</a>, <a href='/commercial-hvac/repair'>emergency repair</a>, and <a href='/commercial-plumbing'>commercial plumbing</a>. You get code-compliant work, documented service, and a single point of contact for scheduling and billing.</p>"],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Do you offer commercial HVAC maintenance contracts?', 'body' => 'Yes. We build custom preventive maintenance contracts with scheduled visits, priority response, and detailed service records — tailored to your equipment and budget so problems get caught before they become emergencies.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'What commercial HVAC systems do you service?', 'body' => 'We install, repair, and maintain packaged rooftop units (RTUs), split and ductless systems, commercial boilers (hydronic and steam), and chillers, plus commercial plumbing. We service all major brands across offices, restaurants, retail, and multi-family properties.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'How quickly can you respond to a commercial HVAC emergency?', 'body' => 'Our team is available 24/7 for commercial HVAC emergencies. Maintenance-contract clients receive priority dispatch, and in most cases we can have a licensed technician on-site the same day across Monmouth, Middlesex, and Ocean counties.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Do you service restaurants and retail in Monmouth County?', 'body' => 'Yes. We work with restaurants, retail stores, and shopping centers throughout Monmouth County — including Freehold, Red Bank, and Middletown — handling rooftop units, make-up air, and refrigeration with scheduling that keeps your doors open for business.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'How much does a commercial HVAC maintenance contract cost?', 'body' => 'Pricing depends on the number and type of units, visit frequency, and facility size, so we quote each plan individually. Most clients find a preventive contract pays for itself by avoiding emergency repairs and downtime. We provide a clear, written proposal upfront.'],
        ];
    }
